Update HTTP link to HTTPS  http://www.nvidia.com redirects to https://www.nvidia.com/, so linking to http is reduntant. More importantly, it could be considered a security issue, do to the nature of plain http. An attacker could perform a MITM attack and redirect the HTTP request to a malicious website. ``` > GET / HTTP/1.1 > Host: www.nvidia.com  Response: < HTTP/1.1 307 Temporary Redirect < Location: https://www.nvidia.com/ ```
